name: Gilligan's Island (Stairway)
comments: The lyrics for the TV show theme are matched with the melody of "Stairway to Heaven". Shortly after the single's release, the song vanished into obscurity following complaints from Atlantic Records (the label Led Zeppelin was signed to at the time) and the writers of the "Gilligan's Island" theme. It later resurfaced on a compilation album in 2000 and the legal issues seem to be resolved now.

name: Brown Girl
comments: In 1979, Peter Herbolzheimer, who had written new arrangements and re-written parts of the music for this version, sued Frank Farian for using the changes and having copied the horn arrangements. 12(!) years later, the highest German civil court (Bundesgerichtshof) ruled in favor of Herbolzheimer. Farian refused to disclose his copyright earnings, though.
